  "datePublished": "2026-03-09",
  "description": "A handout is a player-facing artifact used in a [tabletop role-playing game](../_index.md) to externalize information from the fiction. A handout might be a letter, map fragment, rumor sheet, wanted poster, rules summary, portrait, or inventory list. Its purpose is to give the table a durable object they can point to, reread, and reason from during play.",
